      "system": {
        "description": "<div class=\"boxgroup flexrow boxrow\">\n<div class=\"flexcol box\" style=\"justify-content: flex-start;\">\n<h4 class=\"nogrow\" style=\"margin: 0.5em;\">Features</h4>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 225\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Large snake the length of four or five Junglelanders</p>\n<p>Muddy brown body with the girth of a large pine tree</p>\n<p>Nightmarish long teeth make up the head with no eyes</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"flexcol box\" style=\"justify-content: flex-start;\">\n<h4 class=\"nogrow\" style=\"margin: 0.5em;\">Drives</h4>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 225\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Cool off in the mud</p>\n<p>Feed on fresh meat</p>\n<p>Keep lagoons full of water</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"flexcol box\" style=\"justify-content: flex-start;\">\n<h4 class=\"nogrow\" style=\"margin: 0.5em;\">Tactics</h4>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 225\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Follow fires to find meat</p>\n<p>Rush out from their tunnels for surprise attacks</p>\n<p>Knock down and bite</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 225\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 38\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 41\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 44\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>There are so many serpent-like creatures in the Junglelands, and they are all deadly. The rahara is is a very long and thick serpent whose head is made up almost entirely of its jaws. It has no eyes, just more teeth the length of a Junglelander&rsquo;s forearm.</p>\n<p>The raharas like to dig themselves into the mud and wait for prey to pass close by. We&rsquo;re not sure how they breath while in this position, but they have been known to stay submerged this way for hours at a time. Moreover, we don&rsquo;t know how they detect creatures passing by. It may be a sense of vibrations in the ground, or it could be sound that they follow.</p>\n<p>We know that they have some sort of visual or heat sense because they can latch onto campfires at night from a great distance and often surprise sleeping Junglelanders. Because of this, it is advisable to sleep far away from the fire pit or up in a hammock strung between trees.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Quest Starter:</p>\n<p>A rahara attacked the pigsty of a farmer, decimating the livestock and livelihood of the farmer&rsquo;s family. They are seeking someone to help them eliminate the rahara while its hunger is satiated before it kills the few remaining animals the farmer has.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>Your Truth:</em></p>\n<p><em>It is considered taboo to kill a rahara during a drought because a lagoon or pond never dries up with a rahara in it. Do they have some innate power over water or merely the instinct to find the best source of mud and water?</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>",
